A sprawling vintage-style illustration of an antique wooden cabinet of curiosities, its countless small drawers and compartments all slightly open, each revealing a different glowing miniature mechanical contraption or clockwork invention. The cabinet sits in a warm, sepia-toned study with dust motes floating in afternoon light streaming through a tall window. Some drawers contain tiny spinning gears, others hold crystalline structures or brass instruments. The overall feeling is one of abundant creativity and organized collection, with exactly 105 visible compartments arranged in an intricate honeycomb pattern, each housing its own unique treasure waiting to be discovered.
